2015 HMIS API API documentation version 1.1.0

https://www.hmislynk.com/hmis-clientapi-v2015/rest/v2015

/clients

Operations performed on the set of all HMIS clients within the system, and for adding a new client to the set of clients

/clients get post

get

Searches for client. Returns a list of client ids, based on the query parameters sent. The query parameters are cumulative, so each additional query parameter narrows the search down further.

post

Add a client

get /clients

Searches for client. Returns a list of client ids, based on the query parameters sent. The query parameters are cumulative, so each additional query parameter narrows the search down further.

Secured by oauth_2_0
  • Request
  • Response
  • Security

Query Parameters

  • CreatedAfter: required (string)

    searches for members of the collection created after (inclusive) a particular date

    Example:

    10-11-2011
  • CreatedBefore: required (string)

    searches for members of the collection created before (inclusive) a particular date

    Example:

    10-11-2012
  • UpdatedAfter: required (string)

    searches for members of the collection updated after (inclusive) a particular date

    Example:

    10-11-2011
  • UpdatedBefore: required (string)

    searches for members of the collection updated before (inclusive) a particular date

    Example:

    10-11-2012

/clients/{clientid} get put delete

Operations performed on a single HMIS client within the system.

get

Gets a client using a URI resource parameter/ID.

put

Updates a specific client specified by the URI resource parameter/ID.

delete

Deletes a specific client specified by the URI resource parameter/ID.

get /clients/{clientid}

Gets a client using a URI resource parameter/ID.

Secured by oauth_2_0
  • Request
  • Response
  • Security

URI Parameters

  • clientid: required (string)

    Example:

    ADBC1111211111114111111111D1111V

/clients/{clientid}/enrollments get post

Operations performed on the set of all HMIS enrollments within the system, and for adding a new enrollment to the set of enrollments

get

Searches for enrollment. Returns a list of enrollment ids, based on the query parameters sent. The query parameters are cumulative, so each additional query parameter narrows the search down further.

post

Add a enrollment

get /clients/{clientid}/enrollments

Searches for enrollment. Returns a list of enrollment ids, based on the query parameters sent. The query parameters are cumulative, so each additional query parameter narrows the search down further.

Secured by oauth_2_0

  • Response

    10-11-2012

    searches for members of the collection updated after (inclusive) a particular date

    10-11-2011
  • UpdatedBefore: required (string)

    10-11-2012

/clients/{clientid}/enrollments/{enrollmentid}/enrollmentcocs get post

Operations performed on the set of all HMIS enrollmentcocs within the system, and for adding a new enrollmentcoc to the set of enrollmentcocs

get

Searches for enrollmentcoc. Returns a list of enrollmentcoc ids, based on the query parameters sent. The query parameters are cumulative, so each additional query parameter narrows the search down further.

post

Add a enrollmentcoc

get /clients/{clientid}/enrollments/{enrollmentid}/enrollmentcocs

Searches for enrollmentcoc. Returns a list of enrollmentcoc ids, based on the query parameters sent. The query parameters are cumulative, so each additional query parameter narrows the search down further.

Secured by oauth_2_0
  • Request
  • Response
  • Security

URI Parameters

  • clientid: required (string)

    Example:

    ADBC1111211111114111111111D1111V
  • enrollmentid: required (string)

    Example:

    ADBC1111211111114111111111D1111V

Query Parameters

  • CreatedAfter: required (string)

    searches for members of the collection created after (inclusive) a particular date

    Example:

    10-11-2011
  • CreatedBefore: required (string)

    searches for members of the collection created before (inclusive) a particular date

    Example:

    10-11-2012
  • UpdatedAfter: required (string)

    searches for members of the collection updated after (inclusive) a particular date

    Example:

    10-11-2011
  • UpdatedBefore: required (string)

    searches for members of the collection updated before (inclusive) a particular date

    Example:

    10-11-2012

get

post

get /clients/{clientid}/enrollments/{enrollmentid}/contacts

Searches for contact. Returns a list of contact ids, based on the query parameters sent. The query parameters are cumulative, so each additional query parameter narrows the search down further.

Secured by oauth_2_0
  • Request
  • Response
  • Security

URI Parameters

  • clientid: required (string)

    Example:

    ADBC1111211111114111111111D1111V
  • enrollmentid: required (string)

    Example:

    ADBC1111211111114111111111D1111V

Query Parameters

  • CreatedAfter: required (string)

    searches for members of the collection created after (inclusive) a particular date

    Example:

    10-11-2011
  • CreatedBefore: required (string)

    searches for members of the collection created before (inclusive) a particular date

    Example:

    10-11-2012
  • UpdatedAfter: required (string)

    searches for members of the collection updated after (inclusive) a particular date

    Example:

    10-11-2011
  • UpdatedBefore: required (string)

    searches for members of the collection updated before (inclusive) a particular date

    Example:

    10-11-2012

      "type": "object",
      "properties": {
        "pagination": {
          "type": "object",
          "properties": {
            "from": {
              "type": "integer"

              "type": "integer"
            },
            "total": {
              "type": "integer"
            },
            "maximum": {
              "type": "integer"
            },
            "sort": {
              "type": "object",
              "properties": {}
            }
          },
          "required": [
            "from",
            "returned",
            "total",
            "maximum",
            "sort"
          ]
        },
        "contacts": {
          "type": "array",
          "items": {
            "type": "object",
            "properties": {
              "contactId": {
                "type": "string"
              },
              "contactLocation": {
                "type": "integer"
              }
            },
            "required": [
              "contactId",
              "contactLocation"
            ]
          }
        }
      },
      "required": [
        "pagination",
        "contacts"
      ]
    }
  },
  "required": [
    "contacts"
  ]

/clients/{clientid}/enrollments/{enrollmentid}/employments get post

Operations performed on the set of all HMIS employments within the system, and for adding a new employment to the set of employments

get

Searches for employment. Returns a list of employment ids, based on the query parameters sent. The query parameters are cumulative, so each additional query parameter narrows the search down further.

post

Add a employment

get /clients/{clientid}/enrollments/{enrollmentid}/employments

Searches for employment. Returns a list of employment ids, based on the query parameters sent. The query parameters are cumulative, so each additional query parameter narrows the search down further.

Secured by oauth_2_0
  • Request
  • Response
  • Security

URI Parameters

  • clientid: required (string)

    Example:

    ADBC1111211111114111111111D1111V
  • enrollmentid: required (string)

    Example:

    ADBC1111211111114111111111D1111V

Query Parameters

  • CreatedAfter: required (string)

    searches for members of the collection created after (inclusive) a particular date

    Example:

    10-11-2011
  • CreatedBefore: required (string)

    searches for members of the collection created before (inclusive) a particular date

    Example:

    10-11-2012
  • UpdatedAfter: required (string)

    searches for members of the collection updated after (inclusive) a particular date

    Example:

    10-11-2011
  • UpdatedBefore: required (string)

    searches for members of the collection updated before (inclusive) a particular date

    Example:

    10-11-2012

HTTP status code 200

OK – Everything is working.

Body

Media type: application/json

Type: json

Content:

{
  "$schema": "http://json-schema.org/draft-04/schema#",
  "type": "object",
  "properties": {
    "employments": {
      "type": "object",
      "properties": {
        "pagination": {
          "type": "object",
          "properties": {
            "from": {
              "type": "integer"
            },
            "returned": {
              "type": "integer"
            },
            "total": {
              "type": "integer"
            },
            "maximum": {
              "type": "integer"
            },
            "sort": {
              "type": "object",
              "properties": {}
            }
          },
          "required": [
            "from",
            "returned",
            "total",
            "maximum",
            "sort"
          ]
        },
        "employments": {
          "type": "array",
          "items": {
            "type": "object",
            "properties": {
              "employmentId": {
                "type": "string"
              },
              "employed": {
                "type": "integer"
              },
              "employmentType": {
                "type": "integer"
              },
              "notEmployedReason": {
                "type": "integer"
              },
              "informationDate": {
                "type": "string"
              },
              "dataCollectionStage": {
                "type": "integer"
              }
            },
            "required": [
              "employmentId",
              "employed",
              "employmentType",
              "notEmployedReason",
              "informationDate",
              "dataCollectionStage"
            ]
          }
        }
      },
      "required": [
        "pagination",
        "employments"
      ]
    }
  },
  "required": [
    "employments"
  ]
}

Example:

{
   "employments":{
      "pagination":{
         "from":0,
         "returned":1,
         "total":1,
         "maximum":30,
         "sort":{

         }

            "employmentId":"61fa7069-3d46-4b4f-86f5-44fc4e1d6131",

/clients/{clientid}/enrollments/{enrollmentid}/healthstatuses get post

Operations performed on the set of all HMIS healthstatuses within the system, and for adding a new healthstatus to the set of healthstatuses

get

Searches for healthstatus. Returns a list of healthstatus ids, based on the query parameters sent. The query parameters are cumulative, so each additional query parameter narrows the search down further.

post

Add a healthstatus

get /clients/{clientid}/enrollments/{enrollmentid}/healthstatuses

Searches for healthstatus. Returns a list of healthstatus ids, based on the query parameters sent. The query parameters are cumulative, so each additional query parameter narrows the search down further.

Secured by oauth_2_0
  • Request
  • Response
  • Security

URI Parameters

  • clientid: required (string)

    Example:

    ADBC1111211111114111111111D1111V
  • enrollmentid: required (string)

    Example:

    ADBC1111211111114111111111D1111V

Query Parameters

  • CreatedAfter: required (string)

    searches for members of the collection created after (inclusive) a particular date

    Example:

    10-11-2011
  • CreatedBefore: required (string)

    searches for members of the collection created before (inclusive) a particular date

    Example:

    10-11-2012
  • UpdatedAfter: required (string)

    searches for members of the collection updated after (inclusive) a particular date

    Example:

    10-11-2011
  • UpdatedBefore: required (string)

    searches for members of the collection updated before (inclusive) a particular date

    Example:

    10-11-2012

HTTP status code 200

OK – Everything is working.

Body

Media type: application/json

Type: json

Content:

{
  "$schema": "http://json-schema.org/draft-04/schema#",
  "type": "object",
  "properties": {
    "healthstatuses": {
      "type": "object",
      "properties": {
        "pagination": {
          "type": "object",
          "properties": {
            "from": {
              "type": "integer"
            },
            "returned": {
              "type": "integer"
            },
            "total": {
              "type": "integer"
            },
            "maximum": {
              "type": "integer"
            },
            "sort": {
              "type": "object",
              "properties": {}
            }
          },
          "required": [
            "from",
            "returned",
            "total",
            "maximum",
            "sort"
          ]
        },
        "healthstatuses": {
          "type": "array",
          "items": {
            "type": "object",
            "properties": {
              "healthstatusId": {
                "type": "string"
              },
              "healthCategory": {
                "type": "integer"
              },
              "healthStatus": {
                "type": "integer"

                "type": "string"

              "healthstatusId",
              "healthCategory",
              "healthStatus",
              "informationDate",
              "dataCollectionStage",
              "dueDate"
            ]
          }
        }
      },
      "required": [
        "pagination",
        "healthstatuses"
      ]
    }
  },
  "required": [
    "healthstatuses"
  ]

/clients/{clientid}/enrollments/{enrollmentid}/incomeandsources get post

Operations performed on the set of all HMIS incomeandsources within the system, and for adding a new incomeandsource to the set of incomeandsources

get

Searches for incomeandsource. Returns a list of incomeandsource ids, based on the query parameters sent. The query parameters are cumulative, so each additional query parameter narrows the search down further.

post

Add a incomeandsource

/clients/{clientid}/enrollments/{enrollmentid}/medicalassistances get post

Operations performed on the set of all HMIS medicalassistances within the system, and for adding a new medicalassistance to the set of medicalassistances

get

Searches for medicalassistance. Returns a list of medicalassistance ids, based on the query parameters sent. The query parameters are cumulative, so each additional query parameter narrows the search down further.

post

Add a medicalassistance

get /clients/{clientid}/enrollments/{enrollmentid}/medicalassistances

Searches for medicalassistance. Returns a list of medicalassistance ids, based on the query parameters sent. The query parameters are cumulative, so each additional query parameter narrows the search down further.

Secured by oauth_2_0
  • Request
  • Response
  • Security

URI Parameters

  • clientid: required (string)

    Example:

    ADBC1111211111114111111111D1111V
  • enrollmentid: required (string)

    Example:

    ADBC1111211111114111111111D1111V

Query Parameters

  • CreatedAfter: required (string)

    searches for members of the collection created after (inclusive) a particular date

    Example:

    10-11-2011
  • CreatedBefore: required (string)

    searches for members of the collection created before (inclusive) a particular date

    Example:

    10-11-2012
  • UpdatedAfter: required (string)

    searches for members of the collection updated after (inclusive) a particular date

    Example:

    10-11-2011
  • UpdatedBefore: required (string)

    searches for members of the collection updated before (inclusive) a particular date

    Example:

    10-11-2012

/clients/{clientid}/enrollments/{enrollmentid}/residentialmoveindates get post

Operations performed on the set of all HMIS residentialmoveindates within the system, and for adding a new residentialmoveindate to the set of residentialmoveindates

get

Searches for residentialmoveindate. Returns a list of residentialmoveindate ids, based on the query parameters sent. The query parameters are cumulative, so each additional query parameter narrows the search down further.

post

Add a residentialmoveindate

get /clients/{clientid}/enrollments/{enrollmentid}/residentialmoveindates

Searches for residentialmoveindate. Returns a list of residentialmoveindate ids, based on the query parameters sent. The query parameters are cumulative, so each additional query parameter narrows the search down further.

Secured by oauth_2_0
  • Request
  • Response
  • Security

URI Parameters

  • clientid: required (string)

    Example:

    ADBC1111211111114111111111D1111V
  • enrollmentid: required (string)

    Example:

    ADBC1111211111114111111111D1111V

Query Parameters

  • CreatedAfter: required (string)

    searches for members of the collection created after (inclusive) a particular date

    Example:

    10-11-2011
  • CreatedBefore: required (string)

    searches for members of the collection created before (inclusive) a particular date

    Example:

    10-11-2012
  • UpdatedAfter: required (string)

    searches for members of the collection updated after (inclusive) a particular date

    Example:

    10-11-2011
  • UpdatedBefore: required (string)

    searches for members of the collection updated before (inclusive) a particular date

    Example:

    10-11-2012

/clients/{clientid}/enrollments/{enrollmentid}/entryssvfs get post

Operations performed on the set of all HMIS entryssvfs within the system, and for adding a new entryssvf to the set of entryssvfs

get

Searches for entryssvf. Returns a list of entryssvf ids, based on the query parameters sent. The query parameters are cumulative, so each additional query parameter narrows the search down further.

post

Add a entryssvf

/clients/{clientid}/enrollments/{enrollmentid}/veteraninfos get post

Operations performed on the set of all HMIS veteraninfos within the system, and for adding a new veteraninfo to the set of veteraninfos

get

Searches for veteraninfo. Returns a list of veteraninfo ids, based on the query parameters sent. The query parameters are cumulative, so each additional query parameter narrows the search down further.

post

Add a veteraninfo

/clients/{clientid}/enrollments/{enrollmentid}/exits/{exitid}/exitpaths get post

Operations performed on the set of all HMIS exitpaths within the system, and for adding a new exitpath to the set of exitpaths

get

Searches for exitpath. Returns a list of exitpath ids, based on the query parameters sent. The query parameters are cumulative, so each additional query parameter narrows the search down further.

post

Add a exitpath

get /clients/{clientid}/enrollments/{enrollmentid}/exits/{exitid}/exitpaths

Searches for exitpath. Returns a list of exitpath ids, based on the query parameters sent. The query parameters are cumulative, so each additional query parameter narrows the search down further.

Secured by oauth_2_0
  • Request
  • Response
  • Security

URI Parameters

  • clientid: required (string)

    Example:

    ADBC1111211111114111111111D1111V
  • enrollmentid: required (string)

    Example:

    ADBC1111211111114111111111D1111V
  • exitid: required (string)

    Example:

    ADBC1111211111114111111111D1111V

Query Parameters

  • CreatedAfter: required (string)

    searches for members of the collection created after (inclusive) a particular date

    Example:

    10-11-2011
  • CreatedBefore: required (string)

    searches for members of the collection created before (inclusive) a particular date

    Example:

    10-11-2012
  • UpdatedAfter: required (string)

    searches for members of the collection updated after (inclusive) a particular date

    Example:

    10-11-2011
  • UpdatedBefore: required (string)

    searches for members of the collection updated before (inclusive) a particular date

    Example:

    10-11-2012

HTTP status code 200

OK – Everything is working.

Body

Media type: application/json

Type: json

Content:

{
  "$schema": "http://json-schema.org/draft-04/schema#",
  "type": "object",
  "properties": {
    "exitpaths": {
      "type": "object",
      "properties": {
        "pagination": {
          "type": "object",
          "properties": {
            "from": {
              "type": "integer"
            },
            "returned": {
              "type": "integer"
            },
            "total": {
              "type": "integer"
            },
            "maximum": {
              "type": "integer"
            },
            "sort": {
              "type": "object",
              "properties": {}
            }
          },
          "required": [
            "from",
            "returned",
            "total",
            "maximum",
            "sort"
          ]
        },
        "exitpaths": {
          "type": "array",
          "items": {
            "type": "object",
            "properties": {
              "exitpathId": {
                "type": "string"
              },
              "connectionWithSoar": {
                "type": "integer"
              }
            },
            "required": [
              "exitpathId",
              "connectionWithSoar"
            ]
          }
        }
      },
      "required": [
        "pagination",
        "exitpaths"
      ]
    }
  },
  "required": [
    "exitpaths"
  ]
}

Example:

{
   "exitpaths":{
      "pagination":{
         "from":0,
         "returned":1,
         "total":1,
         "maximum":30,
         "sort":{

         }
      },
      "exitpaths":[
         {
            "exitpathId":"46b4e67b-08f4-4962-9a1e-3ff614aaea23",
            "connectionWithSoar":9
         }

get

  • CreatedAfter: required (string)

    searches for members of the collection created after (inclusive) a particular date

  • CreatedBefore: required (string)

    searches for members of the collection created before (inclusive) a particular date

    Example:

    10-11-2012
  • UpdatedAfter: required (string)

    searches for members of the collection updated after (inclusive) a particular date

    Example:

    10-11-2011
  • UpdatedBefore: required (string)

    searches for members of the collection updated before (inclusive) a particular date

    Example:

    10-11-2012

/projects/funders get post

Operations performed on the set of all HMIS funders within the system, and for adding a new funder to the set of funders

get

Searches for funder. Returns a list of funder ids, based on the query parameters sent. The query parameters are cumulative, so each additional query parameter narrows the search down further.

post

Add a funder

Searches for funder. Returns a list of funder ids, based on the query parameters sent. The query parameters are cumulative, so each additional query parameter narrows the search down further.

    10-11-2012

    searches for members of the collection updated after (inclusive) a particular date

    Example:

    10-11-2011
  • UpdatedBefore: required (string)

    searches for members of the collection updated before (inclusive) a particular date

    Example:

    10-11-2012

/organizations

Operations performed on the set of all HMIS organizations within the system, and for adding a new organization to the set of organizations

/organizations get post

get

Searches for organization. Returns a list of organization ids, based on the query parameters sent. The query parameters are cumulative, so each additional query parameter narrows the search down further.

post

Add a organization

get /organizations

Searches for organization. Returns a list of organization ids, based on the query parameters sent. The query parameters are cumulative, so each additional query parameter narrows the search down further.

Secured by oauth_2_0
  • Request
  • Response
  • Security

Query Parameters

  • CreatedAfter: required (string)

    searches for members of the collection created after (inclusive) a particular date

    Example:

    10-11-2011
  • CreatedBefore: required (string)

    searches for members of the collection created before (inclusive) a particular date

    Example:

    10-11-2012
  • UpdatedAfter: required (string)

    searches for members of the collection updated after (inclusive) a particular date

    Example:

    10-11-2011
  • UpdatedBefore: required (string)

    searches for members of the collection updated before (inclusive) a particular date

    Example:

    10-11-2012

/search

/search/{searchentity} get

get

The Search API is optimized to find the specific entity you're looking for (e.g., a client, enrollments, etc.).It's designed to find the one result you're looking for (or maybe the few results you're looking for). Currently hmislynk supporting search on 'clients' entity only. Just like searching on Google, you sometimes want to see a few pages of search results so that you can find the item that best meets your needs. HMISLynk Search API provides up to 50 results for each searh. However, the search results can be limited by the client. Note: Current supporting URI is /search/clients

get /search/{searchentity}

The Search API is optimized to find the specific entity you're looking for (e.g., a client, enrollments, etc.).It's designed to find the one result you're looking for (or maybe the few results you're looking for). Currently hmislynk supporting search on 'clients' entity only. Just like searching on Google, you sometimes want to see a few pages of search results so that you can find the item that best meets your needs. HMISLynk Search API provides up to 50 results for each searh. However, the search results can be limited by the client. Note: Current supporting URI is /search/clients

Secured by oauth_2_0
  • Request
  • Response
  • Security

URI Parameters

  • searchentity: required (string)

Query Parameters

  • q: required (string)

    The search keywords, as well as any qualifiers. Currently supported search fields are first name,middle name,last name,dob,source system id and ssn. For search on "date of birth" field the format MM-dd-YYYY should be used for the search keyword.

  • sort: required (string)

    The sort field. Default- results are sorted by "created date".

    Example:

    created date
  • order: required (string - default: desc)

    The sort order if sort parameter is provided. One of asc or desc. Default- desc.

    Example:

    desc
  • startIndex: required (integer - default: 0)

    The start Index from where the search results should be returned. Default - 0

    Example:

    0
  • maxItems: required (integer - default: 50)

    the number or Items that should be included in the results . Default - 50

    Example:

    50
  • exclude: required (string)

    Excludes flieds from the search.Currently it suppoted value is "ssi" (to exclude source system id) only.

HTTP status code 200

example: | { "searchResults": { "pagination": { "total":"2" "from": "0", "maximum": "50", "returned":"2" }, "items": [ { "clientId": "65e3df62-dd22-4d07-83ef-6858a6322839", "firstName": "Eric", "middleName": "Eric", "lastName": "Eric", "nameSuffix": "NS ", "nameDataQuality": "1", "ssn": "ssn ", "ssnDataQuality": "1", "dob": "1459498034983", "dobDataQuality": "1", "race": "1", "ethnicity": "1", "gender": "1", "otherGender": "Test", "veteranStatus": "8", "link":"/hmis-clientapi/rest/v2015/clients/65e3df62-dd22-4d07-83ef-6858a6322839" }, { "clientId": "cf98b9b2-9a77-4133-99a3-b60f05a12ad1", "firstName": "Eric", "middleName": "Eric", "lastName": "Eric", "nameSuffix": "NS ", "nameDataQuality": "1", "ssn": "ssn ", "ssnDataQuality": "1", "dob": "1459498034983", "dobDataQuality": "1", "race": "1", "ethnicity": "1", "gender": "1", "otherGender": "Test", "veteranStatus": "8", "link":"/hmis-clientapi/rest/v2014/clients/cf98b9b2-9a77-4133-99a3-b60f05a12ad1" } ] } }
